cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SD 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating the parameters of a planar shape based on a single low-resolution image. This is a common problem in computer vision and image processing, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the effects of several elements on the image formation process, such as point-spread function, discretization step, quantization step, and photon noise, which are related to the fields of graphics (cs.GR), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), and signal processing (cs.SD). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.GR, cs.IT, cs.MM, and cs.SD.
